message.body: How are you doing miss Phuong?

Better I guess, got my car back. Still have the rental. I went from having no car a few days ago to having two now hahah. How's it going on your end? I saw the wedding pics on FB, you and June are looking sharp!
Two cars? That's awesome!! Lol.
I'm good. I'm actually up in Princeton right now. Staying over tonight.
Yea, currently have a Nissan Rogue. I don't think I've ever been in a Nissan Rogue before this.
Oh how come?
That's a nice car. A little more compact.

I was at a training at NY today, and I'll be up here tomorrow, so I decided to just stay here the night. There is a big group here at the hotel, so I wanted to see how the operation runs with a packed house.
Oh fun! It's like a field trip for grown ups!
Are you getting déjà Vu?
Hahaha. Not really...
How's your night going? Any exciting things going on?
Really? It doesn't remind you I when you use to stay there before?
I just got home. Went straight to my sister's house to babysit after I got my car.
How are the boys?!
And I guess it does a little.
It was for housekeeping.
:) Im glad.
They were training me and then I will have to train people.
What's the training about?
They're good! Getting big!!!
Are you training people or are they training you?
Ohhh I see! Oh okay get this, I had a friend invite me to some business event yesterday.
I thought it was like a networking event or something, wasn't exactly clear.
When I came they split us up and like my section got a basic lesson about financial responsibility.
It was pretty much what I learned this past summer.
It was awkward though.
I did not know what my purpose there was.
I usually don't mind those events, but that was off.
You have to probably deal with it often huh?
Yeah. I need to do more training lessons.
How are they? What's it like?
Long usually... About 8 hours. Pretty much a long day of class. Just like school.
Where are you going in NY?
It was earlier today. Staten Island actually
Are you going back there tomorrow?
Nahhh. Just Princeton.
I wonder, are you in the suburbs or more of a metropolitan area?
Does Princeton have a metropolitan area?
Princeton? It's more of a college town. Like Villanova.
You should come see it! Lol
I want to! Are you near the university?
Couple miles away.
I'm so bored... lol
Awww :( it's a prime situation to get comfy in bed, get all cost, snuggle up to a pillow, and watch Netflix :)
lol that's exactly what I'm doing right now.
Hahahah! There ya go! You're a smart cookie ;)
Lol. Hope you're doing the same.
Oh nice. Where at?
I just finished folding laundry. I feel really tired. I want to be doing that. Getting up earlier tomorrow to drive my mom to look at a house.
South Philly. Somehow I think she wants to buy another investment piece, I want to buy a house house. Well that's what my sister said anyways.
Hopefully you'll be able to find a house soon.
I don't want to live during the winter.
*move
Wow, they was dark.
*that
How's that dark?
Ohh. You meant the live part? Lol.
Hahah yea.
You should get some sleep soon if you're getting up early.
Hungry now, going to have a meal hahah.
What did you watch?
The newsroom. Really good show.
You prettying hit all the big ones haven't you? Breaking Bad, House of Cards, now The Newsroom.
*you pretty much hit
You know me. I only watch all the good stuff. lol.
Hahah seems like someone has good taste.
